Subject: [PATCH] branding: replace Chromium icons with Fennec icons

Replaces the Chromium product icon assets in the following locations:
  chrome/app/theme/chromium/           (Linux + Windows)
  chrome/app/theme/chromium/mac/       (macOS .icns)
  chrome/browser/resources/images/     (toolbar / favicon fallbacks)

Icon design specification: see branding/ICON_SPEC.md

TODO: This patch is a stub. Populate with real icon assets once the
      final icon exports are provided by the designer. Place the icon
      files in branding/icons/ and update the GN copy() rules below.

Pixel-perfect requirements per ICON_SPEC.md:
  - Geometric fennec fox head, front-on, flat color
  - Ears: amber (#d4783c), tall isoceles, dominant at 32×32
  - Eyes: light circles, no pupils ("aware but calm")
  - Head: deep warm gray on rounded-square canvas
  - No gradients, no illustrations, no wordmark

PILLAR: Branding
JOURNAL: none

